50|$|In December 2000, the firm’s {{assets were}} {{acquired}} by existing investor Sand Hill Capital. Daniels {{and other key}} executives resigned after disagreeing with Sand Hill {{plans for the future}} direction of the firm. Sand Hill changed the firm’s business-to-business model to a consumer-to-business residential website and subsequently sold the firm to <b>Barry</b> <b>Diller’s</b> InterActiveCorp (IAC).|$|R
